<tr> 
<td bgcolor="#F4F4F4" colspan="2" align="left" valign="top"><p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >The only thing that really needs to be added to game play in my opinion is a donation room feature. Most MUDs have these and they make a lot of sense. They give newbs a chance to have equipment they couldn't otherwise get.<br />
<br />
Restrictions could be placed on the rooms (or NPCs). You couldn't enter if you are over a certain level. You can't remove more than a few items. You can't get stuff for the sake of getting it. Perhaps a <i>random item</i> could be picked from the donations bin upon request and you were only allowed one donation per slot.<br />
<br />
Something to think about.</font></p></td>
</tr>
